## Section 10: Combined Technical / HA-DR / Compliance Scenarios

**91. How do you ensure your Always On AG configuration itself complies with security/audit standards (e.g., endpoint encryption)?**
- Use encrypted database mirroring endpoints between replicas
- Restrict endpoint connect permissions to only the AG service accounts
- Document the AG topology, including security configuration, for audit
- Periodically validate endpoint certificates haven't expired

**92. How do you handle SQL Server licensing compliance audits (Microsoft True-Up)?**
- Maintain an inventory of SQL Server instances, editions, and core counts
- Track licensing model (per-core vs. server+CAL) per environment
- Reconcile against entitlements (EA/agreements) periodically
- Document any virtualization/cloud licensing nuances (e.g., AHB, AWS RDS)

**93. During a SQL Server 2022-to-2025 migration, how do you ensure security/audit configurations carry over correctly?**
- Inventory all security settings (logins, roles, audit specs, TDE, encryption) pre-migration
- Script out and version-control security objects for repeatable deployment
- Validate post-migration via comparison report (pre vs. post state)
- Re-run access certification shortly after migration to confirm consistency

**94. How do you handle a scenario where Cloud (AWS/Azure) hosted SQL databases need to meet the same audit standards as on-prem?**
