- Use native cloud audit/logging (CloudTrail, Azure Monitor) alongside SQL Audit
- Ensure network-level controls (security groups, private endpoints) are documented
- Include cloud resources in the same access review/certification cycle

**95. How would you respond if asked to demonstrate that a downgrade migration (e.g., 2022 to 2017) doesn't reduce your security posture?**
- Inventory security features in use on 2022 that may not exist in 2017 (e.g., certain encryption enhancements)
- Identify compensating controls for any feature gaps
- Document the risk assessment and sign-off for the downgrade decision
- Re-validate audit/compliance configuration post-downgrade

